tracker.name: Epic
tracker.description: Portfolio abstraction of a complex activity that could expand multiple releases. It typically requires an opportunity analysis before the execution decision is taken and it is broken down into "Features" (or minimum market features). Examples: A focal point requirement coming from Opportunity board, a prototype activity, etc.

formElement.name: impediment
formElement.label: Impediment
formElement.description: An impediment is anything preventing optimal progress on a work item. Choose a severity level, and always add a "follow up" comment explaining the reasons and expected actions

item.label: Blocker
item.description: Set this flag if you find a blocking issue. Add a description in the comment field

item.label: Major
item.description: Set this flag if you find an issue causing major delays. Add a description in the follow up field

item.label: Minor
item.description: Set this flag if you find an issue causing a minor delay or inefficiency. Add a description in the follow up field

formElement.name: focal_point_id
formElement.label: Focal Point Id (Url)
formElement.description: URL to the FP requirement. Select "HTML" format if you would like to introduce the link within the Focal Point ID rather than the URL

formElement.name: task_driver
formElement.label: Epic Responsible
formElement.description: Who is the owner / responsible of this Epic

properties.default_value: UDC: CUDB: HLR: HLR-FE: HSS: PG: IPWorks: UPG: UNIV: EIR: OSS: SAPC: Other:

formElement.name: remaining_effort_mh
formElement.label: Remaining Effort (mh)
formElement.description: Remaining effort for the epic. Calculated as sum of the remaining effort for all child elements

properties.default_value: Link to documentation (OP, FCS, report, etc)

formElement.name: details
formElement.label: Original Submission
formElement.description: A full description of the artifact

formElement.name: summary
formElement.label: Summary
formElement.description: One line description of the artifact

formElement.name: category_id
formElement.label: Category
formElement.description: Generally correspond to high level modules or functionalities of your software (e.g. User interface, Configuration Manager, Scheduler, Memory Manager...)

formElement.name: severity
formElement.label: Priority
formElement.description: How quickly the artifact must be completed

formElement.name: stage
formElement.label: Stage
formElement.description: Stage in the life cycle of the artifact

item.label: New
item.description: The artifact has just been submitted

item.label: Analyzed
item.description: The cause of the artifact has been identified and documented

item.label: Accepted
item.description: The artifact will be worked on.

item.label: Under Implementation
item.description: The artifact is being worked on.

item.label: Ready for Review
item.description: Updated/Created non-software work product (e.g. documentation) is ready for review and approval.

item.label: Ready for Test
item.description: Updated/Created software is ready to be included in the next build

item.label: In Test
item.description: Updated/Created software is in the build and is ready to enter the test phase

item.label: Approved
item.description: The artifact fix has been succesfully tested. It is approved and awaiting release.
